node.text:
Happy Sunday, my people ✨🌈 I always felt like I needed to constantly be moving in one direction. However, the past two years, I finally let go…There was a global communal tragic event we all had to endure. I think a lot of us learned a lot from that situation. I learned that in order to heal from some mental health related issues, I need to temporarily put social media on hold. I did put social media on hold and I will again if I need to. Healing comes first. You can only prioritize so many things. Sending love, Jessie ❤️ 
✨art by the incredible @adoseofreminders ! go follow amazing creators like this that are good for your brain 🥺🌈

node.text: nothing prettier than loving and taking time for yourself 🥺 I still have really bad days. I feel like my instagram can make it seem like I’m CONSTANTLY confident in my skin, but that’s not a realistic expectation for ANYONE. I was just watching a youtube video I’m about to upload and considered not posting it because I thought my face looked “puffy”. It’s nearly impossible to NOT feel this way. We’re born into a society where we’ve normalized covering dark circles and having lasers pointed at our stretch marks. I wanted to remind you all that it’s ok if you still have hard days. Some days, you just need to accept your body or tolerate it. Or even some years. Anyways, I LOVE YOU!! ❤️ yours truly, jessie #powmade #friendswithbenefit

node.text: comment a “🍓” if you watched my new youtube video I uploaded last night 🥺 Been working on myself a lot lately. I’m trying to wake up earlier, not be scared to say no to plans, and be more assertive. A huge goal for 2021 was to be a lot more assertive. It’s really hard for me, I learned from a young young age that standing up for myself would result in something bad. When you’re a little kid standing up to an adult, there’s a power in-balance. I’m unlearning a fear of being heard. So much of what I go through is related. With ED Recovery, I learn to take up space. I learn to take care of myself and to put myself first. With feeling more open with showing more of my age and the fact that I’m an adult, I learn that I don’t need to infantilize myself to be more “digestible” to other people. Anyways, I love you!! :) This time I’m asking you for advice. How do you feel more comfortable with confrontation and advocating for yourself? Yours truly, Jessie

I love my body for the first time in a while and I love to show that and somehow that represents how much sex I have?? When a man shows his abs he’s fucking applauded?? it’s 2021, get over it! I’m 22 years old. 90% of you that follow me are used to a Jessie that’s ill. That’s SO HARD for me to comprehend on a daily basis. So I want to show off what I worked hard for and continue to work hard for, which is recovery 🥺
